article.description: Nana Foulland scored 19 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Bucknell routed Army 94-66 on Saturday night for its fourth-straight win.
article.headline: Foulland with 19 points as Bucknell routs Army 94-66
article.linkText: Foulland with 19 points as Bucknell routs Army 94-66
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Nana Foulland scored 19 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Bucknell routed Army 94-66 on Saturday night for its fourth-straight win. D.J. MacLeay added 11 points and Ryan Frazier and Chris Hass had 10 points apiece for the Bison (12-9, 9-1 Patriot League) who finished with a 44-35 rebounding edge over Army (12-9, 3-6). Army had a 13-6 start but Bucknell responded with a 25-8 run capped by a Foulland dunk and a Frazier 3-pointer to go on top 31-21 with 8:53 left in the half. The Bison extended their lead to 53-37 at the break. Frazier sank another 3-pointer to cap a 16-4 run to open the second half and the Bison were up 69-41 with 15:38 to play. They led by 31 points, 87-56, with 7:43 remaining and cruised from there. Luke Morrison scored 13 points and Kyle Wilson had 12 points for Army.
